\subsection{Serie geometrica}

\subsubsection{Definicion}

$\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} r^n = 1 + r + r^2+\cdots$ $r \in \mathbb{R}$

\subsubsection{Teoremas}

$|r| < 1$ $\Rightarrow$ $\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} r^n = \frac{1}{1-r}$ Es convergente

$|r| \geq 1$ $\Rightarrow$ $\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} r^n$ Es divergente

